  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Institutionalizing the phased Approach to Total Sanitation (PhATS) in Local Governance &amp; Programming</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RI strategy addresses the government&apos;s plan to implement  the PhATS (Phased Approach to Total Sanitation) program and transition from direct implementation to a more sustainable government led approach over the next 8 months. The programme aims  to strengthen the institutionalisation of  PhATS within particular within Leyte Province by promoting good governance, improving monitoring and knowledge management, creating inovative solutions, engaging the local community and economy, preparing WASH intervention for emergencies, and building capacity of WASH.</narrative>
  </description>
